description:
Another one of the unfinished targets this year. Have had a long run of pretty horrible astro weather and this one of the targets I was hoping to get lot of data but that didnt happen. I  almost decided to leave it for next year but with no clear weather in the forecast, I processed the data.

Layered the Ha and OIII data with series of stretch to handle the dynamic range from core to halo. This is a good target to go deep to pull structure in the halo. The OIII especially has nicer structure.
I will file the data to add more data next year. 

I also tried shooting at 0 gain but had pretty heavy pattern noise compared to unity (even with very high dither etc). I am going to go back to unity gain... which seems far cleaner IMO

C&C welcome
title: NGC6826 - Blinking Eye
